<item>
            <title>[SPARK-37089] ParquetFileFormat registers task completion listeners lazily, causing Python writer thread to segfault when off-heap vectorized reader is enabled</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-37089</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The task completion listener that closes the vectorized reader is registered lazily in ParquetFileFormat#buildReaderWithPartitionValues(). Since task completion listeners are executed in reverse order of registration, it always runs before the Python writer thread can be interrupted.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This contradicts the assumption in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-37088&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-37088&lt;/a&gt; / &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/34245&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/34245&lt;/a&gt; that task completion listeners are registered bottom-up, preventing that fix from working properly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
